CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper December 26, 1953, pg. 6, reads: "Peoples Cabbies Donate Baskets - Employes [Employees] of Peoples Cab Company donated then bushel baskets of groceries to the Salvation Army here Wednesday in a Christmas gesture.  These groceries were presented by the Captain's Committee which represents the cabmen at Peoples.  Left to right are V. DeFazio, Bud Bender, Louis Impell, president of CIO Local 278; George Kim, Miles Bishop, George McBride, Capt. H. W. Poole of the Salvation Army, and Bill Dobkin. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: V. DeFazio, Bud Bender, Louis Impell, George Kim, Miles Bishop, George McBride, H. W. Poole, and Bill Dobkin gathered around Peoples Cab Company taxi with baskets of food donated to Salvation Army
